The low temperatures of February not only led to losses of millions for the agricultural sector, but they limited the growth opportunities of the state economy, causing a decrease in economic activity by a total of 3.6 percent in the first half of the year, mainly due to a historic fall of 31.16 percent in agriculture, which affected the dynamics of other sectors of the economy.
