Fujimori hospitalized again for medical examination
Former President Alberto Fujimori was admitted to a state hospital on Tuesday to be examined for the loss of muscle strength that is seen in his legs, his family doctor said.
Fujimori, 72, who was sentenced to 25 years in prison for human rights violations committed during his reign (1990-2000), suffers from several diseases, including cancer of the tongue, due to which he was operated on four times and is under surveillance.
