Mujica goes to Mexico to strengthen political ties
The official delegation, led by Uruguayan President José Mujica and consisting of several ministers and businessmen, will arrive in Mexico on Tuesday to boost trade between the two countries and to begin talks on the region's political problems.
Mujica will meet next Wednesday with his Mexican counterpart, Felipe Calderon, the most important point of an extensive plan of meetings with political, commercial authorities and a meeting with the Uruguayan community living in Mexico, according to a timetable published by the Uruguayan leadership.
The meeting of the two presidents in Guadalajara will be “favorable for the exchange of information on the issue of political relations between the two nations,” as the leadership of the South American country published on its website.
